            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>setName</name>
                  <description>Sets a new name for this project with the given name.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>If the given new name is the same as this project's current name then do nothing and exit, else go to the next step.</operation>
                  <operation>Set this project's name to the new name given, emit the name changed signal, and signal this project has been modified.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>newName</name>
                     <description>The new name this project's name is set to.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>setScanDirectory</name>
                  <description>Sets a new scan directory path for this project to the given path. The given path can be relative to this program's present working directory. If the given path is not a valid directory then an exception is thrown.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>If the given path is the same as this project's current scan directory path then do nothing and exit, else go to the next step.</operation>
                  <operation>If the given new path is not a valid directory then throw an exception, else go to the next step.</operation>
                  <operation>Set this project's scan directory to the new path given in its canonical form and signal this project has been modified.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>newPath</name>
                     <description>Path that this project's scan directory is set to.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>setScanFilters</name>
                  <description>Sets new scanning file filters for this project. These filters are used to filter out what files are matched for parsing when a scan thread of this project is used. The filter filters must be separated by spaces.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>If the given scan filters is the same of this project's current scan filters then do nothing and exit, else go to the next step.</operation>
                  <operation>Set this project's scan filters to the new filters given and signal this project has been modified.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>newFilters</name>
                     <description>The file filters that this project will use for scanning.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>save</name>
                  <description>Saves this project to its associated file. If this is a new project that has never been saved then an exception is thrown. If any writing error occurs while saving an exception is thrown.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>If this project has no path to save to then throw an exception, else go to the next step.</operation>
                  <operation>Create a new Qt XML document, appending its XML processing instructions and creating the root project element.</operation>
                  <operation>Save this project's basic information, its type element, and its root block along with all children blocks to the project element.</operation>
                  <operation>Save the Qt XML document as a byte array and save the byte array to this project's file, setting this project as not modified and emitting the saved signal.</operation>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>saveAs</name>
                  <description>Saves this project to a new file with the given path. If any writing error occurs while saving an exception is thrown.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>Set this project's file path to the new path given, changing the file watcher path to the new path given and removing the old one.</operation>
                  <operation>Save this project to the new file. If any exception is thrown while saving then revert this project and its file watcher back to the old path.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>path</name>
                     <description>The path to the new file this project is saved to.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
